      <section eId="sec_CC-3319">
        <num>CC 3319</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-3319__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>By the extinction or destruction of the thing mortgaged.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3319__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>By confusion as a result of the obligee's acquiring ownership of the thing mortgaged.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3319__subsec_3">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p>By prescription of all the obligations that the mortgage secures.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3319__subsec_4">
          <num>(4)</num>
          <content>
            <p>By discharge through execution or other judicial proceeding in accordance with the law.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3319__subsec_5">
          <num>(5)</num>
          <content>
            <p>By consent of the mortgagee.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3319__subsec_6">
          <num>(6)</num>
          <content>
            <p>By termination of the mortgage in the manner provided by Paragraph D of Article 3298.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3319__subsec_7">
          <num>(7)</num>
          <content>
            <p>When all the obligations, present and future, for which the mortgage is established have been incurred and extinguished.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
